text.tspan: Keldling Brew
This is made from organic Pilzner malt, organic
Hallertau Blanch hops and S-33 Dry Brewing yeast.
The malt was mashed in 1° steps from 60°C to 78°C.
Malt and yeast gives it a yellow color (~5 EBC).
The hops adds the bitterness (6.5% Alpha acids)
and some floral/fresh/fruity notes (~35 IBU).
The yeast makes it haze, dry and sweet. It contained
approx. 5% alchohol when bottled on the 20th of
February 2017.
“People of the same trade seldom meet together, even for
merriment and diversion, but the conversation ends in a conspira
cy against the public, or in some contrivance to raise prices.”
- Adam Smith
Professor
Dry
